Detection of outliers using the IQR (Interquartile range) method

In [17]:
p0 = df.Purchase.min()
p100 = df.Purchase.max()
q1 = df.Purchase.quantile(0.25)
q2 = df.Purchase.quantile(0.5)
q3 = df.Purchase.quantile(0.75)
iqr = q3 - q1
In [18]:
lc = q1 - 1.5 * iqr  # lower cutoff
uc = q3 + 1.5 * iqr  # upper cutoff
In [19]:
lc
Out[19]:
-3523.5
In [20]:
uc
Out[20]:
21400.5
In [21]:
print(f"p0 = {p0}, p100 = {p100}, lc = {lc}, uc = {uc}")

p0 = 12, p100 = 23961, lc = -3523.5, uc = 21400.5

If lc < p0 There are NO outliers on the bottom side If uc > p100 There are NO outliers on the higher side

lc < p0, so there are no outliers on the bottom side (-3523.5 < 12). But uc < p100 (21400.5 < 23961), so there are outliers on the higher side. A visual representation of an outlier is provided by a box plot
